E. coli K-12 does not contain an afuA ortholog.

ecocyc_summary: Comment from EcoGene: Two independent insertions, IS30C and IS2D, interrupt ydbA. The IS2D insertion is in codon 839 and made a 5 bp target site duplication AACCC. The IS30C insertion is in codon 856 and made a 2 bp target site duplication CT. The pre-insertion YdbA sequence has been reconstructed and is consistent with the sequence of a closely-related E. coli 53638 protein with this region intact (NCBI gi 75515008). The first 21 aa of YdbA are predicted to be a type I signal peptide. The 17 codons between the two insertions encode PELTYADSGAKIVNKGT and were overlooked in previous reconstructions.
name: b1401
